<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3923] Make the datatype optional when declaring columns with generation clauses</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3923</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;According to the ANSI/ISO spec, the datatype is supposed to be optional for columns defined by generation clauses. This elegant shorthand is a stretch goal.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
